C++ code solves the problem of finding the shortest path to collect all keys in a grid. It uses a BFS approach to explore the grid. It initializes the start position and a bitmask to track collected keys. 

It checks if the position contains a key or a lock and updates the key state accordingly. It also keeps track of visited positions with different key states to avoid revisiting them. If all keys are collected, it returns the shortest distance. 

