For making a graph bipartite any two of it's adjacent node should come under two different sections.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
- Denoting two different section as two different colors (here, 1 & -1).
- Implementing dfs and start coloring the graph.
- Coloring every adjacent node of current node with opposite color of current node.
- If two adjacent nodes are encountered with same colour then return false, because in this case making this graph bipartite is not possible.
- If whole graph is coloured, then this graph can be bipartite, so return true.
